CHAT.comment: 1. Past tense is now usually signalled. Some irregular past participles are correct , e.g. "You went to football". In some cases , "-d" or "-d" is added to the irregular participle , e.g. "camed [: came] [* +ed-sup]" , "broked" , but "breaked" is also used. 2. Syllable final "l" is replaced by short rounded close back vowel dialectally in most cases. There is one recorded instance of "wheel" and of "ball" with a final voiced lateral approximant. 3. There is confusion over the meanings of "today" and "tomorrow" which are used interchangeably , and of "big" and "small" , which are used together to describe the same thing. 4. Lucy is still using "my" and "mine" for "I" at times , but there are more instances of "I" being used in subject position.
